UPDATE locales_page_Text SET text_loc8='<HTML>
<BODY>
<BR/>
<P>This time I was awake! It was very vivid, and yet for over a minute, in the middle of the warm, sunny day, my breath came out misted and chill. One of the priests noticed and dropped to his knees in prayer.</P>
<BR/>
<P>No one else heard the voice, though. At least the witness proves that I\'m not going insane. Maybe I should ask Landgren to pray on the matter?</P>
<BR/>
<P>I\'ll get Jordan and Street to scrutinize their recruiting efforts tomorrow. We\'ve grown bloated with ranks of unbelievers who yearn only to destroy the undead. That\'s not enough!</P>
</BODY>
</HTML>
' WHERE entry=3135; /* text: <HTML>
<BODY>
<BR/>
<P>This time I was awake! It was very vivid, and yet for over a minute, in the middle of the warm, sunny day, my breath came out misted and chill. One of the priests noticed and dropped to his knees in prayer.</P>
<BR/>
<P>No one else heard the voice, though. At least the witness proves that I\'m not going insane. Maybe I should ask Landgren to pray on the matter?</P>
<BR/>
<P>I\'ll get Jordan and Street to scrutinize their recruiting efforts tomorrow. We\'ve grown bloated with ranks of unbelievers who yearn only to destroy the undead. That\'s not enough!</P>
</BODY>
</HTML> */
UPDATE locales_page_Text SET text_loc8='<HTML>
<BODY>
<BR/>
<P>The commander and the bishop were both receptive. Not that they had any choice. Bishop Street in particular seemed very enthusiastic. He spoke of a revival for the crusade and swore to ferret out the weak of faith within our ranks.</P>
<BR/>
<P>I told him to go easy. I\'ve no intention of destroying the Crusade. However, I do like the sound of forming an elite cadre of the most faithful to do the Light\'s bidding in Northrend. I fear the man\'s friendship with LeCraft is slowly twisting him. They both have their uses, though.</P>
</BODY>
</HTML>
' WHERE entry=3136; /* text: <HTML>
